Got it — here's the broader operational picture: the day-to-day work items, tickets, and incidents a CyberArk PAM/EPM team actually deals with, not just the scripting side.

**Daily Operational Work Items (PAM)**

- Onboarding/offboarding privileged accounts as users join, leave, or change roles
- Processing access requests — granting, extending, revoking safe access
- Password reset requests when users get locked out or a rotation fails mid-session
- Break-glass/emergency access requests (someone needs privileged access urgently, outside normal approval flow)
- Safe creation requests from application/infra teams for new systems
- Reviewing and approving dual-control access requests
- Coordinating with server/app teams when a discovered account needs an owner assigned
- Periodic access recertification — chasing managers/owners to confirm still-needed access
- Vendor/third-party privileged access provisioning and time-boxing

**Common Incidents (PAM)**

- **Failed password rotation** — account locked out, CPM couldn't change password on target (permissions issue, account locked, network unreachable)
- **PVWA/PSM unavailability** — users can't log in or launch sessions, usually infra/certificate/service related
- **Vault connectivity issues** — CPM or PVWA losing connection to the vault
- **Session recording failures** — compliance risk if sessions aren't being recorded
- **Account lockouts** — target account locked due to failed rotation attempts or someone manually changing the password outside CyberArk ("password out of sync")
- **Orphaned safes/accounts** — decommissioned servers/apps still holding active privileged accounts, flagged in audits
- **Certificate expiry incidents** — PVWA/PSM certs expiring causing outages
- **Failed backup jobs** — vault backup didn't complete, needs troubleshooting
- **Unauthorized access attempts** — flagged by SIEM, needs investigation (was this legitimate, misuse, or a true incident)
- **License/component capacity issues** — hitting session or component limits during peak usage

**Daily Operational Work Items (EPM)**

- Reviewing and approving/denying elevation requests submitted by end users
- Onboarding new applications into allow-list/elevation policies
- Handling user complaints — "my app got blocked and I need it to run"
- Policy exception requests (temporary elevation for a specific task/project)
- Coordinating with endpoint/desktop teams on agent deployment issues

**Common Incidents (EPM)**

- **Agent offline/not reporting** — endpoint not communicating with EPM server
- **Legitimate business app blocked** — policy too restrictive, causing user disruption, needs urgent exception
- **Malware/suspicious elevation attempt** — event that needs security team investigation
- **Policy rollout breaking production apps** — a new policy pushed too broadly causes multiple app failures
- **Agent version incompatibility** — after OS patching/updates, agent misbehaves or crashes

**What's Automatable vs. What Stays Manual/Human-Judgment**

| Automatable | Needs Human Judgment |
|---|---|
| Rotation failure detection & ticket creation | Break-glass access approval |
| Access request SLA reminders | Suspicious session investigation |
| Orphaned account flagging | Deciding to grant policy exceptions |
| Agent offline detection | Incident root-cause on outages |
| Recertification report generation | Vendor access risk decisions |
| Routine onboarding via ticket trigger | Malware/security event triage |

